==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Saccharine
<hw>Sac"cha*rine</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A trade name for benzoic sulphinide.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>saccharin</asp>.]</altsp> <-- A synthetic
sweetening agent used (in the form of the sodium salt) as a non-caloric
sweetening agent, to avoid gaining weight or for medical purposes.
Benzoic sulfimide, <chform>C7H5NO3S</chform>. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saccharinic</ent>⟦br⟧
